<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-04-21T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-04-21T00:00:00-05:00" n="531" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d531">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 837.00/1318</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-04-21">
                                    <hi rend="italic">April 21, 1917</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>General Gustavo Caballero, former governor of Camaguey, was seriously
                            wounded and 150 of his followers taken prisoners by Colonel Pujol today.
                            Caballero has been operating between Camaguey and Manatí in Oriente. In
                            an encounter three days ago 40 of his men were killed.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gonzales</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
